The girl doesn't know if she should laugh or cry. He grabs another blackberry and offers it to her. "Here, maybe this will make you feel better. How long have you been out here?" The girl wipes her tears and responds. "Well, I was walking my usual way home and then I got lost. Do you- do you think you could help me find my way?" The girl is hesitant, but at this point, she just wants to find any way home. The bear smiles and stands up. He reaches his paw out to her. "Of course, I know these woods like they're the back of my paw. Come on, I'll get you back home safely." The little girl feels encouraged and gets up. This time, she doesn't hesitate and grabs the bear's hand. The bear finds her home and the girl is relieved. She hugs the bear. "Thank you! I'm home!" The bear smiles and says, "If you get lost again, you can find me by the blackberry bushes." 

