Assistant: Natalia tried not to make it too obvious that she was staring, but there was little doubt of it. And she knew, when her friend Madison started grinning widely at her that she had best give up the pretense and ask like she wanted to. 

“Who is that?” Natalia murmured as she fluttered the fan in front of her face, hiding the movement of her mouth. 

Madison grinned from behind her own, brightly colored fan and the twinkle in her eye unsettled Natalia.

“That’s Mr. Ainsely,” she said with the kind of confidence she always held when it came to gossip, “He may not be all that much to look at, but he’s filthy rich and has won more battles than all of the knights in the kingdom combined.”

“Mr Ainsley? He isn’t a knight himself?”

Madison shook her head, “No. A contracted, medaled soldier during the last war, but he switched professions after it ended.”

“Your ability to dig up information can honestly be terrifying sometimes. Do you happen to know what he does now?”

“For that comment I don’t think I’ll tell you.” Though the smile she sent Natalia said otherwise. “Oh, but I’ll let you off the hook this time. I don’t know. No one seems to know. He won’t talk about it apparently.”

“How’d he make his fortune?”

Madison shrugged. “Another mystery.” 

Natalia considered that for a moment. “I think he’s alright.”

