Assistant: Just two weeks ago, Peter, a baby bird, made his grand entrance into the world. After being nurtured by his mother and father, it was almost time for Peter to venture out of the nest. The world outside the nest was unchartered territory, and Peter was anxious about making the jump. 

Peter's parents started nudging him and his siblings toward the edge of the nest, so they can get a better view of the world. It was a beautiful place, but there were so many noises and things moving around. To say it was daunting would be an understatement. But, Peter was intrigued. 

One by one, Peter's siblings made the venture outside the nest. They would come back to visit a few times a day. They told him that the world was a great place and that they were having so much fun exploring. 

Peter decided it was time to be brave and join his parents and siblings outside the nest. He slowly stepped to the very edge. However, upon looking down he realized just how high up he was. He cautiously moved back into the center of the nest. His mother and father saw this and decided to head to the nest. They assured him that they would be there to help. Peter agreed to give it a go. Back on the edge, he began flapping his wings. He took a deep breath and made the daring jump. Much to his surprise, he was flying with ease.

Peter saw his parents and siblings foraging around in some grass just below the tree he was in. He swooped down with ease to join them. He was delighted to see that they were in an area with abundant flying insects. With one quick jump, he caught an insect. He was so proud to be able to catch his own meals. He realized that while he had to be cautious in a world that can be quite dangerous, it was a fantastic place to explore and live. 

