Assistant: Most plants love the sun, but many beautiful shade-loving flowers could be perfect in your garden. Here are some options for plants that will provide vivid color, but don’t need that much sun:

- Impatiens: Coming in a variety of colors and hues, impatiens bloom in spring and summer. Too much sun can wilt them, so a shade garden is a perfect spot.
- Bleeding Hearts: These unique, heart-shaped flowers produce their fullest blooms in a shady spot.
- Rhododendron: Unlike many plants, these flowering shrubs thrive under the cover of trees in rich, moist soil.
- Lungwort: If you are looking for something that spreads, this is a great option. Lungwort loves the shade and produces lovely pink and violet flowers.
- Fuchsia: This plant produces trailing, teardrop-shaped flowers. Fuchsia hates the harsh sun, so a shady spot will keep it very happy.
- Foxgloves: These plants produce tall, elegant flower clusters in a wide variety of colors. They can handle some sun in cooler climates, but they thrive in shade.

