Assistant: To: longlostfriend@friends.com
From: friend@friends.com
Subject: Wow!

Friend! I haven't seen you in years. Thank you for giving your information to my secretary while you were in town. Sorry I couldn't talk long, I had a meeting I needed to get to and I was running late, but now I have time to talk a bit.

How have you been? Where have you been? The last time I saw you was when we were in high school together, and we went to the beach on senior skip day. That was a fun day!

I'll fill you in on what I've been up to since then. After high school, I went to college but dropped out a semester later and found a job to make some money. I was working in sales for three years before I ended up starting my own business selling electronics from home, and now I run a big company that has locations worldwide. You stopped by my main office the other day and spoke to my secretary; we also have offices in the UK, China, Japan, and Thailand. We even have a satellite office close to where you live in Green Acres. You're welcome to check it out if you like.

I used to be married but now I'm divorced (long story) and we have three children, two of whom live with me and the other going to college. I'm hoping once the older one is finished with her schooling, she will consider working for my company to learn the ropes and take over when I'm retired.

Have you kept up with any of our friends from high school? I haven't seen any of them for a long time. You're the first person I've talked to from high school since then! I'm glad you reached out to me, it's always cool to walk down memory lane.

If you ever want to talk more, you now have my email. I'll also give you my number below. Hope to hear from you soon man!

Your Friend
(000) 800-0000

