Assistant: POV 1: Sarah
Is it possible for a couple to make it when both of them aren't morning people? I just had yet *another* stupid fight with Alfred, and I don't even know how or why it got started. Maybe it's because I haven't had my morning coffee yet. But this is seriously ruining my day. Can't we both just go about our mornings like the proper sleepy zombies that we are, say something nice to each other, eat our breakfast, then go to work? Instead, Alfred has to nitpick at everything. How did we even get onto the topic of dinosaurs? And more importantly, the tyrannosaurus rex is clearly the superior dinosaur to velociraptors for anyone who hasn't been brainwashed by Jurassic Park. Whatever. I'm gonna make him cook dinner tonight to make it up to me.

POV 2: Alfred
Every morning I wake up more in love with Sarah and more convinced than ever that we are soulmates. At this point, I don't even remember how I managed to wake up and go to work with even half my brain cells active when I was without her. But now that I have her by my side, I can always count on her to come up with the most whimsical topics to make my mornings better. For example, this morning, I was barely able to keep my eyes open. But one spirited debate about T-rexes vs. velociraptors later (for the record, velociraptors are the superior dinosaurs), and I'm wide awake and ready for work. Who needs coffee when you have the best girlfriend in the world? I think, to show my appreciation for her later on, I'm going to cook her a romantic dinner tonight. And who knows? Maybe it's time for me to propose to her too. Any girl you can argue dinosaurs about in the morning has to be a keeper!

