-	2-3 serrano or jalapeno peppers, diced
-	Chili powder and cumin (optional)

Cut up all the non-spicy ingredients as necessary. If you prefer, you can use a food processor to speed up the chopping process. Taste-test it to determine how much salt, pepper, and lime juice is necessary. Once you’re satisfied, divide your salsa into two containers and set one aside. It's best to store the non-spicy portion away before you cut up your spicy ingredients just to make sure you don't accidentally add them where they don't belong.

The remaining half will be your spicy salsa. Chop your chilis and spicy peppers and add them as necessary. Note that serrano or jalapeno peppers do not always have consistent levels of spice, so you may want to start with one pepper and test how hot it tastes. Add as much as you feel is necessary. 

