tinker_cookbook.supervised.train:259 [[92mINFO[0m] <|begin_of_text|>User: Write an uplifting message for someone who is having a hard time.

Assistant: If you are going through a rough time right now, remember that you are not alone. When we are surrounded by darkness and despair, we can often feel like we are separated from the rest of humanity. In reality, getting lost in hard and trying times is something that most of us will experience many times in our lives. Even when you may feel as though you will never find the light again, persevere, and one day you will be glad that you did.

In life, all things are cyclical, including our downfalls and our blessings. Sometimes, the passage through the darkness can seem long and unending, but you must have faith that the good days will indeed come again. On difficult days, look for the smallest flecks of light you can find. Whether it be a pretty flower, a funny joke on social media, or a well-intended message from a friend, all of these things can serve as tiny sparks to help you maintain hope in your future.

It is okay to have a bad day. It is okay to have a bad week. It is okay to have a bad month. It is okay to have a bad year. These things do not mean that you will have a bad life. Take time to care for yourself and work to keep yourself alive through the hard days. One day, the clouds will clear, and you should be around to see the sun again.

