The boy grabbed a book from the shelf, the cover so faded he couldn't even read the title. As he read the pages, his mind raced. With every turn, his excitement grew. As he reached the final chapter, he almost couldn't contain his joy anymore! How could this story possibly end? And then, slowly, it was over. This book, like many others on the shelf, was so badly damaged that many of its pages were illegible. He returned the book to its home, likely the last time it will ever be read. As the boy left the library, he looked back longingly. One day, he'd finish these stories, but not today.

