tinker_cookbook.supervised.train:259 [[92mINFO[0m] <|begin_of_text|>User: I want to make bagels but I've never done it before. Can you walk me through a simple recipe teaching me how to make bagels? List the steps numerically.

Assistant: Step 1: First, you will want to take 1/2 cup of warm water and put it into a bowl. Take 2 tablespoons of active yeast and 4 tablespoons of sugar and stir them into the water. Let it sit for 5 minutes until the yeast proofs. 
Step 2: In another bowl, combine 3 cups of flour (you can add more as needed) and 1.5 tablespoons of salt and stir them until combined.
Step 3: Pour the flour and salt into the yeast mixture. Add another 1/3 cup of warm water and stir the mixture until it starts to form a dough.
Step 4: Flour a clean countertop and knead your dough until it is smooth and elastic. This can take around 10 minutes to get a firm dough.
Step 5: Coat a bowl and the ball of dough with oil. Place the dough ball in the bowl and cover it with a damp towel.
Step 6: Let your dough rise for an hour.
Step 7: Once the dough has doubled in size, punch down and allow it to rise again for another 10 minutes.
Step 8: Cut your dough into 8 equal pieces. Shape each piece of dough into a round ball. 
Step 9: Coat your finger in flour and push a hole through the center of each dough ball. Stretch the hole about a third of the bagel's diameter.
Step 10: Bring a pot of water to a boil. Once it's at a boil, place each (as many as will fit at a time) bagel into the water and boil for 1-2 minutes on both sides. once they are done, placed them onto an oiled baking sheet.
Step 11: Repeat step 10 until all bagels have been boiled. Preheat your oven to 425F. 
Step 12: Place the tray of bagels into the oven and allow to bake for 20 minutes.
Step 13: Once the bagels are golden brown, take them out and allow them to cool. 


