Assistant: Hello [name]!

I hope this finds you well. I’m writing to you about an opportunity I’d like to share with you and your school community. 

I sell children’s books – mainly picture books for ages 3+. I used to do this as a part-time job but now do it primarily because I love books and believe so much in the importance of stories and reading for kids. I’m an English teacher with a six-year-old son, and, being in education and seeing the influence that books have had on him and his growth, feel very strongly that reading should be much more accessible to children and families. I buy them as cheaply as possible so that I can keep costs very reasonable ($3-$10 with the average price of a picture book being $5). All books are in very good condition (some gently used and some new).

Due to a recent job change, I don’t do this as much as I used to but, this year, during August, I’ll be going around to pre-schools that are interested and setting up my book table during either drop-off or pick-up for parents and families to buy. I also give a 20% discount to teachers. If you would be interested in offering this to your parents and families (and teachers!), let me know, and I can send you the specific dates I have available.

Many thanks for your time.

[name]


