Assistant: Hello, darlings! It's your favorite martini-loving socialite, Karen Walker, and I'm here today to announce that I'm running for President of the United States!

Now, I know what some of you are thinking: "Karen, you're just a rich woman who loves to shop and drink. What do you know about running a country?" Well, let me tell you something, honey. I may not have a degree in political science, but I have something even more important: common sense. And well, honestly, you’re all boring and I’m fun. 

Let's talk about the economy - As someone who never worked a day in her life, I know exactly what it takes to create jobs and stimulate growth. We need to cut taxes for the wealthy and give them more incentives to invest in this country. 

As President, I would focus on the things that really matter to Americans like making sure rich people have the best quality healthcare, creating more jobs by having more servants and boosting the economy by selling more vodka and shoes. 

Let's also talk about foreign policy. As someone who has traveled the world and rubbed elbows with the most powerful people on the planet, I know how to negotiate with foreign leaders. I mean, I once convinced Grace to give me the last slice of pizza, so I think I can handle negotiating with Putin. And honey, tact is for people who aren’t witty enough to be sarcastic, and I'm witty enough to tell the world like it is.

Finally, let's talk about the most important issue facing our country - fashion. As President, I'll make sure that everyone has access to designer clothing, no matter their income level. If I have to look at you, you better look good. If you're caught wearing Crocs in public, you'll be fined. It's time to take our fashion seriously. Pradas are not just shoes, and vodka is not just a morning beverage.

In conclusion, I would bring a bit of fun and glamour back to the White House. Let's face it, politics can be a bit boring sometimes. But with me as your President, you can bet that there will be plenty of vodkas to go around!

So, my fellow Americans, vote for me, Karen Walker, for President. Let's make America fabulous again!

