2. French Quarter. This neighborhood is the heart and soul of New Orleans as well as a National Historic Landmark. The site of the original New Orleans colony established in 1718 by the French, this area retains much of its original charm with French street names, narrow cobblestone streets, and various historic attractions. The French Quarter is a suitable choice based on your interest in historic locations. 
3. National WWII Museum. The museum has an array of artifacts and educational films covering all aspects of World War II. One of the most interesting features is the oral recantations of both civilian and soldier experiences during the early 1940s. This destination should suit you based on your interest in museums. 

