tinker_cookbook.supervised.train:259 [[92mINFO[0m] <|begin_of_text|>User: Write a blog post for me about a day of work in the office. I work as an IT support specialist. Nothing too long, 5 paragraphs at most. Try to make it a bit funny and use the name Jim.

Assistant: Is it Friday yet? What another long and dull day at work. I don't dislike my job or the people I work with but some days just drag and get to you, know what I mean? Yeah, well, if you haven't figured it out yet today was one of those days for me.

It started well enough. I got into my car, got my morning Starbucks, and hit the ground running with a smile on my face. I clocked in at 8 a.m. but by 9 o'clock I was ready to be done. The first call I had to handle was from the receptionist whose computer wouldn't turn on. I talked it over with her for 15 minutes before I left my desk to take a look in person. She hadn't hit the power button. Yeah, it was hard not to face-palm that one. And that was the best call of the day!

They had me running all over. It wasn't only the people on my floor that had issues but I even got called up to the C-Suite to fix the COO's laptop that wasn't working. He couldn't access the internet. Well, maybe it would have helped if he hit the Wi-Fi button first! It was just problem after problem. I know that's my job but I also like a bit of a challenge, you know, the kind that lets me use my mind and skills.

But still, dealing with silly tech issues is the name of the game and isn't what set me off course. It was my co-worker who called in sick and left me with this mess. It was the lunch order that arrived cold and soggy. I mean, how hard is it to get a good slice of cheese pizza? And you know what, looking back on it, it was that Starbucks barista who couldn't even spell my name right. Jim. Yeah, my name is Jim, not Gym.

Well anyway, it's time to stop this rant here. Works not all bad but some days it helps to vent. Tomorrow will be better, brighter, and I'm going to get another slice of pizza and it's going to be delicious.

